Good hotpot place! About NT200 for weekday lunch though over when you choose the soup base (NT10 for basic Japanese seaweed broth to NT80 for milk based which is not meant to be drank unless cooked first). Bowl of veggies is OK portion as is the meats (about six slices pork). Sauces have variety you can add yourself and also has free sodas, soft serve ice cream, and on-site freshly made noodle machines (thin cooks in 2-3 min or thick cooks in 5-6 min. Select portion first and push button making sure to have plate below to catch it). Other items on menu also good. Seafood was fresh when we ordered it and regular orders (ie, not business lunch) have good portions. Air con is on high so it doesn’t feel hot when eating in summer. * Has special free meat if rate five stars on Google Map but I still give it 5 for the fresh good portion foods and nice environment. Service is pretty good too with the waitstaff I met. It’s a relatively new restaurant opened July 2020 and I have been there four times already (10/2020).  ** Update Jan 2021: still really good! :) Now has Uber Eats and Foodpanda deliveries. Kids under 120 cm add NT30 per child. Over that and will have to order either lunch pot or about NT200 on other items (can share with adult if non-lunch pots). Free indoor parking of 3 or 5 hours at the carrefour building (make sure to get parking stub at restaurant counter).

The weather is getting colder and colder. If you come to a hot pot at this time, it is really super happy (hahaha)~ This is a house I saw by chance when I rented a house nearby, and the sales are better than average. Small hot pots with small portions are actually like the "screaming x addiction" or "xma stinky pot" seen in the market. When it was first opened, there were not many crowds. Later, I followed my roommate a few times. Decided to try it. Surprisingly, I found it was quite delicious, the environment was quite clean, and the service was quite good. There were ice drinks but only two kinds. One type of winter melon tea is iced tea. In addition, there are also ice creams available. The four flavors are basically strawberry, chocolate, Swiss chocolate, and yogurt. Although it is not a big brand, I think the taste and taste are not bad. The point is that the price of 150 can be a good choice, but I also have to I said that I recently went shopping and found that it has risen by five yuan 😅 but the taste has not changed, and it has been maintained 👍 It’s just that I have a bad feeling when I went to eat this time. I told the aunt outside the store that I had dinner for two, and the aunt replied that it was good. I just talked to my friend. Waiting outside, unexpectedly, after waiting for about 15 minutes, a couple came into the shop and told her that they immediately saw a seat and took a seat. The aunt did not stop or make any other actions, but directly helped each other order food, which made me see I was very confused and unhappy, so I asked the aunt directly, and the reply was that I didn't tell her to have a meal. Even if it is true, the guests stand at the door and keep watching and do not actively ask? Suddenly I was quite happy when I came back to the neighborhood and wanted to make a special trip to have a meal. The mood became very bad. Especially during the epidemic, I know very well and understand this kind of hard work. After all, I have had this experience before. Therefore, I think it is necessary to be more cautious and careful to manage every detail. I will still Those who go to consume and dine only hope to improve the problem and solve the problem if there is a problem, and hope that there will be no such bad feelings when visiting again, otherwise it would be quite a pity.
